    {
      "id": "time",
      "icon": "🕐",
      "title": "Telling time",
      "subtitle": "Il-Ħin — what time is it?",
      "intro": "Maltese has no word for 'o'clock' — you just say the number. Note: 1 and 2 use special forms (is-siegħa, is-sagħtejn). For everything else, the cardinal number with the article.",
      "facts": [
        "Filgħodu = AM (morning).",
        "Wara nofsinhar = PM (afternoon, after 12 noon).",
        "Filgħaxija = evening (roughly 6pm to 10pm).",
        "Ta' billejl = night (after 10pm).",
        "There's no Maltese word for 'o'clock' — just the number with its article."
      ],
